3368
3369int ipf_parsefile(fd, addfunc, iocfuncs, filename)
3370int fd;
3371addfunc_t addfunc;
3372ioctlfunc_t *iocfuncs;
3373char *filename;
3374{
3375 FILE *fp = NULL;
3376 char *s;
3377
3378 ipf_yylineNum = 1;
3379 ipf_yysettab(ipfwords);
3380
3381 s = getenv("YYDEBUG");
3382 if (s != NULL)
3383 ipf_yydebug = atoi(s);
3384 else
3385 ipf_yydebug = 0;
3386
3387 if (strcmp(filename, "-")) {
3388 fp = fopen(filename, "r");
3389 if (fp == NULL) {
3390 fprintf(stderr, "fopen(%s) failed: %s\n", filename,
3391 STRERROR(errno));
3392 return -1;
3393 }
3394 } else
3395 fp = stdin;
3396
3397 while (ipf_parsesome(fd, addfunc, iocfuncs, fp) == 1)
3398 ;
3399 if (fp != NULL)
3400 fclose(fp);
3401 return 0;
3402}
3403
3404
3405int ipf_parsesome(fd, addfunc, iocfuncs, fp)
3406int fd;
3407addfunc_t addfunc;
3408ioctlfunc_t *iocfuncs;
3409FILE *fp;
3410{
3411 char *s;
3412 int i;
3413
3414 ipffd = fd;
3415 for (i = 0; i <= IPL_LOGMAX; i++)
3416 ipfioctls[i] = iocfuncs[i];
3417 ipfaddfunc = addfunc;
3418
3419 if (feof(fp))
3420 return 0;
3421 i = fgetc(fp);
3422 if (i == EOF)
3423 return 0;
3424 if (ungetc(i, fp) == 0)
3425 return 0;
3426 if (feof(fp))
3427 return 0;
3428 s = getenv("YYDEBUG");
3429 if (s != NULL)
3430 ipf_yydebug = atoi(s);
3431 else
3432 ipf_yydebug = 0;
3433
3434 ipf_yyin = fp;
3435 ipf_yyparse();
3436 return 1;
3437}

3439
3440static void newrule()
3441{
3442 frentry_t *frn;
3443
3444 frn = allocfr();
3445 for (fr = frtop; fr != NULL && fr->fr_next != NULL; fr = fr->fr_next)
3446 ;
3447 if (fr != NULL) {
3448 fr->fr_next = frn;
3449 frn->fr_pnext = &fr->fr_next;
3450 }
3451 if (frtop == NULL) {
3452 frtop = frn;
3453 frn->fr_pnext = &frtop;
3454 }
3455 fr = frn;
3456 frc = frn;
3457 fr->fr_loglevel = 0xffff;
3458 fr->fr_isc = (void *)-1;
3459 fr->fr_logtag = FR_NOLOGTAG;
3460 fr->fr_type = FR_T_NONE;
3461 fr->fr_flineno = ipf_yylineNum;
3462
3463 if (use_inet6 == 1)
3464 fr->fr_family = AF_INET6;
3465 else if (use_inet6 == -1)
3466 fr->fr_family = AF_INET;
3467
3468 nrules = 1;
3469}

3471
3472static void setipftype()
3473{
3474 for (fr = frc; fr != NULL; fr = fr->fr_next) {
3475 if (fr->fr_type == FR_T_NONE) {
3476 fr->fr_type = FR_T_IPF;
3477 fr->fr_data = (void *)calloc(sizeof(fripf_t), 1);
3478 fr->fr_dsize = sizeof(fripf_t);
3479 fr->fr_family = frc->fr_family;
3480 if (fr->fr_family == AF_INET) {
3481 fr->fr_ip.fi_v = 4;
3482 }
3483 else if (fr->fr_family == AF_INET6) {
3484 fr->fr_ip.fi_v = 6;
3485 }
3486 fr->fr_mip.fi_v = 0xf;
3487 fr->fr_ipf->fri_sifpidx = -1;
3488 fr->fr_ipf->fri_difpidx = -1;
3489 }
3490 if (fr->fr_type != FR_T_IPF) {
3491 fprintf(stderr, "IPF Type not set\n");
3492 }
3493 }
3494}

3496
3497static frentry_t *addrule()
3498{
3499 frentry_t *f, *f1, *f2;
3500 int count;
3501
3502 for (f2 = frc; f2->fr_next != NULL; f2 = f2->fr_next)
3503 ;
3504
3505 count = nrules;
3506 f = f2;
3507 for (f1 = frc; count > 0; count--, f1 = f1->fr_next) {
3508 f->fr_next = allocfr();
3509 if (f->fr_next == NULL)
3510 return NULL;
3511 f->fr_next->fr_pnext = &f->fr_next;
3512 added++;
3513 f = f->fr_next;
3514 *f = *f1;
3515 f->fr_next = NULL;
3516 if (f->fr_caddr != NULL) {
3517 f->fr_caddr = malloc(f->fr_dsize);
3518 bcopy(f1->fr_caddr, f->fr_caddr, f->fr_dsize);
3519 }
3520 }
3521
3522 return f2->fr_next;
3523}

3525
3526static int
3527lookuphost(name, addrp)
3528 char *name;
3529 i6addr_t *addrp;
3530{
3531 int i;
3532
3533 hashed = 0;
3534 pooled = 0;
3535 dynamic = -1;
3536
3537 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3538 if (fr->fr_ifnames[i] == -1)
3539 continue;
3540 if (strcmp(name, fr->fr_names + fr->fr_ifnames[i]) == 0) {
3541 ifpflag = FRI_DYNAMIC;
3542 dynamic = addname(&fr, name);
3543 return 1;
3544 }
3545 }
3546
3547 if (gethost(AF_INET, name, addrp) == -1) {
3548 fprintf(stderr, "unknown name \"%s\"\n", name);
3549 return -1;
3550 }
3551 return 0;
3552}

3554
3555static void dobpf(v, phrase)
3556int v;
3557char *phrase;
3558{
3559#ifdef IPFILTER_BPF
3560 struct bpf_program bpf;
3561 struct pcap *p;
3562#endif
3563 fakebpf_t *fb;
3564 u_32_t l;
3565 char *s;
3566 int i;
3567
3568 for (fr = frc; fr != NULL; fr = fr->fr_next) {
3569 if (fr->fr_type != FR_T_NONE) {
3570 fprintf(stderr, "cannot mix IPF and BPF matching\n");
3571 return;
3572 }
3573 fr->fr_family = vtof(v);
3574 fr->fr_type = FR_T_BPFOPC;
3575
3576 if (!strncmp(phrase, "0x", 2)) {
3577 fb = malloc(sizeof(fakebpf_t));
3578
3579 for (i = 0, s = strtok(phrase, " \r\n\t"); s != NULL;
3580 s = strtok(NULL, " \r\n\t"), i++) {
3581 fb = realloc(fb, (i / 4 + 1) * sizeof(*fb));
3582 l = (u_32_t)strtol(s, NULL, 0);
3583 switch (i & 3)
3584 {
3585 case 0 :
3586 fb[i / 4].fb_c = l & 0xffff;
3587 break;
3588 case 1 :
3589 fb[i / 4].fb_t = l & 0xff;
3590 break;
3591 case 2 :
3592 fb[i / 4].fb_f = l & 0xff;
3593 break;
3594 case 3 :
3595 fb[i / 4].fb_k = l;
3596 break;
3597 }
3598 }
3599 if ((i & 3) != 0) {
3600 fprintf(stderr,
3601 "Odd number of bytes in BPF code\n");
3602 exit(1);
3603 }
3604 i--;
3605 fr->fr_dsize = (i / 4 + 1) * sizeof(*fb);
3606 fr->fr_data = fb;
3607 return;
3608 }
3609
3610#ifdef IPFILTER_BPF
3611 bzero((char *)&bpf, sizeof(bpf));
3612 p = pcap_open_dead(DLT_RAW, 1);
3613 if (!p) {
3614 fprintf(stderr, "pcap_open_dead failed\n");
3615 return;
3616 }
3617
3618 if (pcap_compile(p, &bpf, phrase, 1, 0xffffffff)) {
3619 pcap_perror(p, "ipf");
3620 pcap_close(p);
3621 fprintf(stderr, "pcap parsing failed (%s)\n", phrase);
3622 return;
3623 }
3624 pcap_close(p);
3625
3626 fr->fr_dsize = bpf.bf_len * sizeof(struct bpf_insn);
3627 fr->fr_data = malloc(fr->fr_dsize);
3628 bcopy((char *)bpf.bf_insns, fr->fr_data, fr->fr_dsize);
3629 if (!bpf_validate(fr->fr_data, bpf.bf_len)) {
3630 fprintf(stderr, "BPF validation failed\n");
3631 return;
3632 }
3633#endif
3634 }
3635
3636#ifdef IPFILTER_BPF
3637 if (opts & OPT_DEBUG)
3638 bpf_dump(&bpf, 0);
3639#else
3640 fprintf(stderr, "BPF filter expressions not supported\n");
3641 exit(1);
3642#endif
3643}

3650 dynamic = -1;

3667
3668static int
3669makepool(list)
3670 alist_t *list;
3671{
3672 ip_pool_node_t *n, *top;
3673 ip_pool_t pool;
3674 alist_t *a;
3675 int num;
3676
3677 if (list == NULL)
3678 return 0;
3679 top = calloc(1, sizeof(*top));
3680 if (top == NULL)
3681 return 0;
3682
3683 for (n = top, a = list; (n != NULL) && (a != NULL); a = a->al_next) {
3684 if (use_inet6 == 1) {
3685#ifdef AF_INET6
3686 n->ipn_addr.adf_family = AF_INET6;
3687 n->ipn_addr.adf_addr = a->al_i6addr;
3688 n->ipn_addr.adf_len = offsetof(addrfamily_t,
3689 adf_addr) + 16;
3690 n->ipn_mask.adf_family = AF_INET6;
3691 n->ipn_mask.adf_addr = a->al_i6mask;
3692 n->ipn_mask.adf_len = offsetof(addrfamily_t,
3693 adf_addr) + 16;
3694
3695#endif
3696 } else {
3697 n->ipn_addr.adf_family = AF_INET;
3698 n->ipn_addr.adf_addr.in4.s_addr = a->al_1;
3699 n->ipn_addr.adf_len = offsetof(addrfamily_t,
3700 adf_addr) + 4;
3701 n->ipn_mask.adf_family = AF_INET;
3702 n->ipn_mask.adf_addr.in4.s_addr = a->al_2;
3703 n->ipn_mask.adf_len = offsetof(addrfamily_t,
3704 adf_addr) + 4;
3705 }
3706 n->ipn_info = a->al_not;
3707 if (a->al_next != NULL) {
3708 n->ipn_next = calloc(1, sizeof(*n));
3709 n = n->ipn_next;
3710 }
3711 }
3712
3713 bzero((char *)&pool, sizeof(pool));
3714 pool.ipo_unit = IPL_LOGIPF;
3715 pool.ipo_list = top;
3716 num = load_pool(&pool, ipfioctls[IPL_LOGLOOKUP]);
3717
3718 while ((n = top) != NULL) {
3719 top = n->ipn_next;
3720 free(n);
3721 }
3722 return num;
3723}
3724
3725
3726static u_int makehash(list)
3727alist_t *list;
3728{
3729 iphtent_t *n, *top;
3730 iphtable_t iph;
3731 alist_t *a;
3732 int num;
3733
3734 if (list == NULL)
3735 return 0;
3736 top = calloc(1, sizeof(*top));
3737 if (top == NULL)
3738 return 0;
3739
3740 for (n = top, a = list; (n != NULL) && (a != NULL); a = a->al_next) {
3741 if (a->al_family == AF_INET6) {
3742 n->ipe_family = AF_INET6;
3743 n->ipe_addr = a->al_i6addr;
3744 n->ipe_mask = a->al_i6mask;
3745 } else {
3746 n->ipe_family = AF_INET;
3747 n->ipe_addr.in4_addr = a->al_1;
3748 n->ipe_mask.in4_addr = a->al_2;
3749 }
3750 n->ipe_value = 0;
3751 if (a->al_next != NULL) {
3752 n->ipe_next = calloc(1, sizeof(*n));
3753 n = n->ipe_next;
3754 }
3755 }
3756
3757 bzero((char *)&iph, sizeof(iph));
3758 iph.iph_unit = IPL_LOGIPF;
3759 iph.iph_type = IPHASH_LOOKUP;
3760 *iph.iph_name = '\0';
3761
3762 if (load_hash(&iph, top, ipfioctls[IPL_LOGLOOKUP]) == 0)
3763 sscanf(iph.iph_name, "%u", &num);
3764 else
3765 num = 0;
3766
3767 while ((n = top) != NULL) {
3768 top = n->ipe_next;
3769 free(n);
3770 }
3771 return num;
3772}
3773
3774
3775int ipf_addrule(fd, ioctlfunc, ptr)
3776int fd;
3777ioctlfunc_t ioctlfunc;
3778void *ptr;
3779{
3780 ioctlcmd_t add, del;
3781 frentry_t *fr;
3782 ipfobj_t obj;
3783
3784 if (ptr == NULL)
3785 return 0;
3786
3787 fr = ptr;
3788 add = 0;
3789 del = 0;
3790
3791 bzero((char *)&obj, sizeof(obj));
3792 obj.ipfo_rev = IPFILTER_VERSION;
3793 obj.ipfo_size = fr->fr_size;
3794 obj.ipfo_type = IPFOBJ_FRENTRY;
3795 obj.ipfo_ptr = ptr;
3796
3797 if ((opts & OPT_DONOTHING) != 0)
3798 fd = -1;
3799
3800 if (opts & OPT_ZERORULEST) {
3801 add = SIOCZRLST;
3802 } else if (opts & OPT_INACTIVE) {
3803 add = (u_int)fr->fr_hits ? SIOCINIFR :
3804 SIOCADIFR;
3805 del = SIOCRMIFR;
3806 } else {
3807 add = (u_int)fr->fr_hits ? SIOCINAFR :
3808 SIOCADAFR;
3809 del = SIOCRMAFR;
3810 }
3811
3812 if ((opts & OPT_OUTQUE) != 0)
3813 fr->fr_flags |= FR_OUTQUE;
3814 if (fr->fr_hits)
3815 fr->fr_hits--;
3816 if ((opts & OPT_VERBOSE) != 0)
3817 printfr(fr, ioctlfunc);
3818
3819 if ((opts & OPT_DEBUG) != 0) {
3820 binprint(fr, sizeof(*fr));
3821 if (fr->fr_data != NULL)
3822 binprint(fr->fr_data, fr->fr_dsize);
3823 }
3824
3825 if ((opts & OPT_ZERORULEST) != 0) {
3826 if ((*ioctlfunc)(fd, add, (void *)&obj) == -1) {
3827 if ((opts & OPT_DONOTHING) == 0) {
3828 char msg[80];
3829
3830 sprintf(msg, "%d:ioctl(zero rule)",
3831 fr->fr_flineno);
3832 return ipf_perror_fd(fd, ioctlfunc, msg);
3833 }
3834 } else {
3835#ifdef USE_QUAD_T
3836 printf("hits %qd bytes %qd ",
3837 (long long)fr->fr_hits,
3838 (long long)fr->fr_bytes);
3839#else
3840 printf("hits %ld bytes %ld ",
3841 fr->fr_hits, fr->fr_bytes);
3842#endif
3843 printfr(fr, ioctlfunc);
3844 }
3845 } else if ((opts & OPT_REMOVE) != 0) {
3846 if ((*ioctlfunc)(fd, del, (void *)&obj) == -1) {
3847 if ((opts & OPT_DONOTHING) == 0) {
3848 char msg[80];
3849
3850 sprintf(msg, "%d:ioctl(delete rule)",
3851 fr->fr_flineno);
3852 return ipf_perror_fd(fd, ioctlfunc, msg);
3853 }
3854 }
3855 } else {
3856 if ((*ioctlfunc)(fd, add, (void *)&obj) == -1) {
3857 if ((opts & OPT_DONOTHING) == 0) {
3858 char msg[80];
3859
3860 sprintf(msg, "%d:ioctl(add/insert rule)",
3861 fr->fr_flineno);
3862 return ipf_perror_fd(fd, ioctlfunc, msg);
3863 }
3864 }
3865 }
3866 return 0;
3867}

3882
3883static void fillgroup(fr)
3884frentry_t *fr;
3885{
3886 frentry_t *f;
3887
3888 for (f = frold; f != NULL; f = f->fr_next) {
3889 if (f->fr_grhead == -1 && fr->fr_group == -1)
3890 break;
3891 if (f->fr_grhead == -1 || fr->fr_group == -1)
3892 continue;
3893 if (strcmp(f->fr_names + f->fr_grhead,
3894 fr->fr_names + fr->fr_group) == 0)
3895 break;
3896 }
3897
3898 if (f == NULL)
3899 return;
3900
3901 /*
3902 * Only copy down matching fields if the rules are of the same type
3903 * and are of ipf type. The only fields that are copied are those
3904 * that impact the rule parsing itself, eg. need for knowing what the
3905 * protocol should be for rules with port comparisons in them.
3906 */
3907 if (f->fr_type != fr->fr_type || f->fr_type != FR_T_IPF)
3908 return;
3909
3910 if (fr->fr_family == 0 && f->fr_family != 0)
3911 fr->fr_family = f->fr_family;
3912
3913 if (fr->fr_mproto == 0 && f->fr_mproto != 0)
3914 fr->fr_mproto = f->fr_mproto;
3915 if (fr->fr_proto == 0 && f->fr_proto != 0)
3916 fr->fr_proto = f->fr_proto;
3917
3918 if ((fr->fr_mproto == 0) && ((fr->fr_flx & FI_TCPUDP) == 0) &&
3919 ((f->fr_flx & FI_TCPUDP) != 0)) {
3920 fr->fr_flx |= FI_TCPUDP;
3921 fr->fr_mflx |= FI_TCPUDP;
3922 }
3923}

3960char *varname, *value;
3961{
3962
3963 if (!strcasecmp(value, "true")) {
3964 do_tuneint(varname, 1);

3966 do_tuneint(varname, 0);

3968 ipf_yyerror("did not find true/false where expected");
3969 }

3986
3987static int addname(frp, name)
3988frentry_t **frp;
3989char *name;
3990{
3991 frentry_t *f;
3992 int nlen;
3993 int pos;
3994
3995 nlen = strlen(name) + 1;
3996 /*
3997 * realloc is harder to use here because the end of the structure
3998 * needs to be zero'd, else it gets junk bytes.
3999 */
4000 f = calloc(1, (*frp)->fr_size + nlen);
4001 memcpy(f, *frp, (*frp)->fr_size);
4002 free(*frp);
4003 if (*frp == frc)
4004 frc = f;
4005 *frp = f;
4006 if (f == NULL)
4007 return -1;
4008 if (f->fr_pnext != NULL)
4009 *f->fr_pnext = f;
4010 f->fr_size += nlen;
4011 pos = f->fr_namelen;
4012 f->fr_namelen += nlen;
4013 strcpy(f->fr_names + pos, name);
4014 f->fr_names[f->fr_namelen] = '\0';
4015 return pos;
4016}

4081static void
4082build_dstaddr_af(fp, ptr)
4083 frentry_t *fp;
4084 void *ptr;
4085{
4086 struct ipp_s *ipp = ptr;
4087 frentry_t *f = fp;
4088
4089 if (f->fr_family != AF_UNSPEC && ipp->f == AF_UNSPEC) {
4090 ipp->f = f->fr_family;
4091 ipp->v = f->fr_ip.fi_v;
4092 }
4093 if (ipp->f == AF_INET)
4094 ipp->v = 4;
4095 else if (ipp->f == AF_INET6)
4096 ipp->v = 6;
4097
4098 for (; f != NULL; f = f->fr_next) {
4099 f->fr_ip.fi_dst = ipp->a;
4100 f->fr_mip.fi_dst = ipp->m;
4101 f->fr_family = ipp->f;
4102 f->fr_ip.fi_v = ipp->v;
4103 f->fr_mip.fi_v = 0xf;
4104 f->fr_datype = ipp->type;
4105 if (ipp->ifpos != -1)
4106 f->fr_ipf->fri_difpidx = ipp->ifpos;
4107 }
4108 fr = NULL;
4109}

4143#define ipf_yydepth (int)(ipf_yystack.s_mark - ipf_yystack.s_base)

4155/* allocate initial stack or double stack size, up to YYMAXDEPTH */
4156static int ipf_yygrowstack(YYSTACKDATA *data)
4157{
4158 int i;
4159 unsigned newsize;
4160 YYINT *newss;
4161 YYSTYPE *newvs;
4162#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4163 YYLTYPE *newps;
4164#endif
4165
4166 if ((newsize = data->stacksize) == 0)
4167 newsize = YYINITSTACKSIZE;
4168 else if (newsize >= YYMAXDEPTH)
4169 return YYENOMEM;
4170 else if ((newsize *= 2) > YYMAXDEPTH)
4171 newsize = YYMAXDEPTH;
4172
4173 i = (int) (data->s_mark - data->s_base);
4174 newss = (YYINT *)realloc(data->s_base, newsize * sizeof(*newss));
4175 if (newss == 0)
4176 return YYENOMEM;
4177
4178 data->s_base = newss;
4179 data->s_mark = newss + i;
4180
4181 newvs = (YYSTYPE *)realloc(data->l_base, newsize * sizeof(*newvs));
4182 if (newvs == 0)
4183 return YYENOMEM;
4184
4185 data->l_base = newvs;
4186 data->l_mark = newvs + i;
4187
4188#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4189 newps = (YYLTYPE *)realloc(data->p_base, newsize * sizeof(*newps));
4190 if (newps == 0)
4191 return YYENOMEM;
4192
4193 data->p_base = newps;
4194 data->p_mark = newps + i;
4195#endif
4196
4197 data->stacksize = newsize;
4198 data->s_last = data->s_base + newsize - 1;
4199
4200#if YYDEBUG
4201 if (ipf_yydebug)
4202 fprintf(stderr, "%sdebug: stack size increased to %d\n", YYPREFIX, newsize);
4203#endif
4204 return 0;
4205}

4270int
4271YYPARSE_DECL()
4272{
4273 int ipf_yym, ipf_yyn, ipf_yystate, ipf_yyresult;
4274#if YYBTYACC
4275 int ipf_yynewerrflag;
4276 YYParseState *ipf_yyerrctx = NULL;
4277#endif /* YYBTYACC */
4278#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4279 YYLTYPE ipf_yyerror_loc_range[3]; /* position of error start/end (0 unused) */
4280#endif
4281#if YYDEBUG
4282 const char *ipf_yys;
4283
4284 if ((ipf_yys = getenv("YYDEBUG")) != 0)
4285 {
4286 ipf_yyn = *ipf_yys;
4287 if (ipf_yyn >= '0' && ipf_yyn <= '9')
4288 ipf_yydebug = ipf_yyn - '0';
4289 }
4290 if (ipf_yydebug)
4291 fprintf(stderr, "%sdebug[<# of symbols on state stack>]\n", YYPREFIX);
4292#endif
4293#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4294 memset(ipf_yyerror_loc_range, 0, sizeof(ipf_yyerror_loc_range));
4295#endif
4296
4297#if YYBTYACC
4298 ipf_yyps = ipf_yyNewState(0); if (ipf_yyps == 0) goto ipf_yyenomem;
4299 ipf_yyps->save = 0;
4300#endif /* YYBTYACC */
4301 ipf_yym = 0;
4302 ipf_yyn = 0;
4303 ipf_yynerrs = 0;
4304 ipf_yyerrflag = 0;
4305 ipf_yychar = YYEMPTY;
4306 ipf_yystate = 0;
4307
4308#if YYPURE
4309 memset(&ipf_yystack, 0, sizeof(ipf_yystack));
4310#endif
4311
4312 if (ipf_yystack.s_base == NULL && ipf_yygrowstack(&ipf_yystack) == YYENOMEM) goto ipf_yyoverflow;
4313 ipf_yystack.s_mark = ipf_yystack.s_base;
4314 ipf_yystack.l_mark = ipf_yystack.l_base;
4315#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4316 ipf_yystack.p_mark = ipf_yystack.p_base;
4317#endif
4318 ipf_yystate = 0;
4319 *ipf_yystack.s_mark = 0;
4320
4321ipf_yyloop:
4322 if ((ipf_yyn = ipf_yydefred[ipf_yystate]) != 0) goto ipf_yyreduce;
4323 if (ipf_yychar < 0)
4324 {
4325#if YYBTYACC
4326 do {
4327 if (ipf_yylvp < ipf_yylve)
4328 {
4329 /* we're currently re-reading tokens */
4330 ipf_yylval = *ipf_yylvp++;
4331#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4332 ipf_yylloc = *ipf_yylpp++;
4333#endif
4334 ipf_yychar = *ipf_yylexp++;
4335 break;
4336 }
4337 if (ipf_yyps->save)
4338 {
4339 /* in trial mode; save scanner results for future parse attempts */
4340 if (ipf_yylvp == ipf_yylvlim)
4341 { /* Enlarge lexical value queue */
4342 size_t p = (size_t) (ipf_yylvp - ipf_yylvals);
4343 size_t s = (size_t) (ipf_yylvlim - ipf_yylvals);
4344
4345 s += YYLVQUEUEGROWTH;
4346 if ((ipf_yylexemes = (YYINT *)realloc(ipf_yylexemes, s * sizeof(YYINT))) == NULL) goto ipf_yyenomem;
4347 if ((ipf_yylvals = (YYSTYPE *)realloc(ipf_yylvals, s * sizeof(YYSTYPE))) == NULL) goto ipf_yyenomem;
4348#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4349 if ((ipf_yylpsns = (YYLTYPE *)realloc(ipf_yylpsns, s * sizeof(YYLTYPE))) == NULL) goto ipf_yyenomem;
4350#endif
4351 ipf_yylvp = ipf_yylve = ipf_yylvals + p;
4352 ipf_yylvlim = ipf_yylvals + s;
4353#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4354 ipf_yylpp = ipf_yylpe = ipf_yylpsns + p;
4355 ipf_yylplim = ipf_yylpsns + s;
4356#endif
4357 ipf_yylexp = ipf_yylexemes + p;
4358 }
4359 *ipf_yylexp = (YYINT) YYLEX;
4360 *ipf_yylvp++ = ipf_yylval;
4361 ipf_yylve++;
4362#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4363 *ipf_yylpp++ = ipf_yylloc;
4364 ipf_yylpe++;
4365#endif
4366 ipf_yychar = *ipf_yylexp++;
4367 break;
4368 }
4369 /* normal operation, no conflict encountered */
4370#endif /* YYBTYACC */
4371 ipf_yychar = YYLEX;
4372#if YYBTYACC
4373 } while (0);
4374#endif /* YYBTYACC */
4375 if (ipf_yychar < 0) ipf_yychar = YYEOF;
4376#if YYDEBUG
4377 if (ipf_yydebug)
4378 {
4379 if ((ipf_yys = ipf_yyname[YYTRANSLATE(ipf_yychar)]) == NULL) ipf_yys = ipf_yyname[YYUNDFTOKEN];
4380 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: state %d, reading token %d (%s)",
4381 YYDEBUGSTR, ipf_yydepth, ipf_yystate, ipf_yychar, ipf_yys);
4382#ifdef YYSTYPE_TOSTRING
4383#if YYBTYACC
4384 if (!ipf_yytrial)
4385#endif /* YYBTYACC */
4386 fprintf(stderr, " <%s>", YYSTYPE_TOSTRING(ipf_yychar, ipf_yylval));
4387#endif
4388 fputc('\n', stderr);
4389 }
4390#endif
4391 }
4392#if YYBTYACC
4393
4394 /* Do we have a conflict? */
4395 if (((ipf_yyn = ipf_yycindex[ipf_yystate]) != 0) && (ipf_yyn += ipf_yychar) >= 0 &&
4396 ipf_yyn <= YYTABLESIZE && ipf_yycheck[ipf_yyn] == (YYINT) ipf_yychar)
4397 {
4398 YYINT ctry;
4399
4400 if (ipf_yypath)
4401 {
4402 YYParseState *save;
4403#if YYDEBUG
4404 if (ipf_yydebug)
4405 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: CONFLICT in state %d: following successful trial parse\n",
4406 YYDEBUGSTR, ipf_yydepth, ipf_yystate);
4407#endif
4408 /* Switch to the next conflict context */
4409 save = ipf_yypath;
4410 ipf_yypath = save->save;
4411 save->save = NULL;
4412 ctry = save->ctry;
4413 if (save->state != ipf_yystate) YYABORT;
4414 ipf_yyFreeState(save);
4415
4416 }
4417 else
4418 {
4419
4420 /* Unresolved conflict - start/continue trial parse */
4421 YYParseState *save;
4422#if YYDEBUG
4423 if (ipf_yydebug)
4424 {
4425 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: CONFLICT in state %d. ", YYDEBUGSTR, ipf_yydepth, ipf_yystate);
4426 if (ipf_yyps->save)
4427 fputs("ALREADY in conflict, continuing trial parse.\n", stderr);
4428 else
4429 fputs("Starting trial parse.\n", stderr);
4430 }
4431#endif
4432 save = ipf_yyNewState((unsigned)(ipf_yystack.s_mark - ipf_yystack.s_base + 1));
4433 if (save == NULL) goto ipf_yyenomem;
4434 save->save = ipf_yyps->save;
4435 save->state = ipf_yystate;
4436 save->errflag = ipf_yyerrflag;
4437 save->ipf_yystack.s_mark = save->ipf_yystack.s_base + (ipf_yystack.s_mark - ipf_yystack.s_base);
4438 memcpy (save->ipf_yystack.s_base, ipf_yystack.s_base, (size_t) (ipf_yystack.s_mark - ipf_yystack.s_base + 1) * sizeof(YYINT));
4439 save->ipf_yystack.l_mark = save->ipf_yystack.l_base + (ipf_yystack.l_mark - ipf_yystack.l_base);
4440 memcpy (save->ipf_yystack.l_base, ipf_yystack.l_base, (size_t) (ipf_yystack.l_mark - ipf_yystack.l_base + 1) * sizeof(YYSTYPE));
4441#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
4442 save->ipf_yystack.p_mark = save->ipf_yystack.p_base + (ipf_yystack.p_mark - ipf_yystack.p_base);
4443 memcpy (save->ipf_yystack.p_base, ipf_yystack.p_base, (size_t) (ipf_yystack.p_mark - ipf_yystack.p_base + 1) * sizeof(YYLTYPE));
4444#endif
4445 ctry = ipf_yytable[ipf_yyn];
4446 if (ipf_yyctable[ctry] == -1)
4447 {
4448#if YYDEBUG
4449 if (ipf_yydebug && ipf_yychar >= YYEOF)
4450 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: backtracking 1 token\n", YYDEBUGSTR, ipf_yydepth);
4451#endif
